cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.CE, cs.DB

The paper deals with a problem in machine learning (clustering) and utilizes information theory concepts. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The problem also involves handling large datasets, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as the second likely sub-category. The use of information theory concepts such as the Chernoff Information and large-deviation principle suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as the third likely sub-category. The paper also deals with the problem of clustering sequences, which suggests cs.CE (Computational Biology and Bioinformatics) as the fourth likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of clustering contigs, which suggests cs.DB (Databases) as the fifth likely sub-category.
